tilly talking about our armor, our weapons, how tov drops are determined, etc.  It was an informative conversation to say the very least.<br><br>EW paladin 1260 ac with a 24 22 1hs and shield (prob 4 pieces kael)<br>ToV paladin 1220 ac with a 2hs but no shield (almost full kael)<br>Me paladin 1160 ac with a 27 29 1hs and shield. (2 pieces skyshrine)<br><br>We talked about our gear, paladin equipment, skyshrine quest armor vs kael quest armor, weapon selection, paladin vs warrior for tanking adds, etc, for a long long time.  At one point one of the casters in the group said &quot;this is why you never put 3 paladins in a group together&quot;<br><br>The question is: When the tanks in your group (guild/raid/whatever) start talking stats, drops, and everything else under the sun, and start pulling out the 25 foot measuring tape, what do most of you think of it?  Do you think that the tanks who are discussing these things are only loot driven, selfish people?  Or do you think it is natural for them to try and learn from each other?  or do you just sit back, try and relax, and see if you can pick up any new tidbits of information that you do not know pop up in the conversation?<br><br><br>Dammur<br>55 Paladin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uvibesjoker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ViBeSJoKeR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Matahari GM</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/7/01 4:57:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=567.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.eqmatahari.com/images/vibes1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span cla